        // About Section
        'about-title': 'About Beheira Governorate',
        'about-text': 'Beheira is one of Egypt\'s governorates located in the northern part of the country in the Nile Delta. It is distinguished by its strategic location, rich history, and unique cultural diversity.',
        'about-p1': 'Beheira Governorate is located in the northern part of the Arab Republic of Egypt in the Nile Delta, bordered to the north by the Mediterranean Sea, to the east by the Rosetta branch, to the west by Alexandria Governorate, and to the south by Giza Governorate.',
        'about-p2': 'The governorate is famous for its unique tourism diversity, combining religious tourism (Coptic monasteries in Wadi El Natrun), historical tourism (archaeological landmarks in Rosetta), and environmental tourism (natural lakes and reserves).',
        'about-p3': 'Rosetta, the famous historical city, is the crown jewel of Beheira Governorate with its unique archaeological houses and the Rosetta Stone, which was the key to deciphering ancient Egyptian civilization.',
        
